The Yadgir Town Police have arrested six persons, who allegedly assaulted Paul Madhukar, District Superintendent of Methodist Church, here on Saturday.The police said that Mr. Madhukar was allegedly assaulted by six followers of the church soon after a meeting, held by Bishop Subhod Mandol, to discuss Mr. Madhukarâ€™s transfer concluded.Some people had staged a dharna outside the church recently demanding the transfer of Mr. Madhukar, they added.Meanwhile, a counter case against Mr. Madhukar was also filed, the police said and added that inquiry into the issue was on.